    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2433651162" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2433651162" />
    <a title="Kenneth White-Spunner" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/83407023-kenneth-white-spunner"><img alt="Kenneth White-Spunner" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2433651162?book_show_action=true">Jun 23, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kenneth White-Spunner" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kenneth White-Spunner" href="/user/show/83407023-kenneth-white-spunner">Kenneth White-Spunner</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2433651162" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17731258326034453966">Human nature seems to dictate that we over-complicate the profound. We have a million words to describe something that in essence is outrageously simple: God. At times I found myself crying tears of joy while reading “Be Still &amp; Listen”, for the words of Amos Smith were exactly what was in my heart. And those words don’t belong to Amos or myself, but to God. Amos has the rare ability to take the profound and explain it in a way that we can all understand, a true teacher at heart! He is my spirit</span>
  <span id="freeText17731258326034453966" style="display:none">Human nature seems to dictate that we over-complicate the profound. We have a million words to describe something that in essence is outrageously simple: God. At times I found myself crying tears of joy while reading “Be Still &amp; Listen”, for the words of Amos Smith were exactly what was in my heart. And those words don’t belong to Amos or myself, but to God. Amos has the rare ability to take the profound and explain it in a way that we can all understand, a true teacher at heart! He is my spiritual brother &amp; another of God’s gifts to the world.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="17731258326034453966" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


